Great Migrations gives new meaning to the word 'move'.
This masterful seven -part series takes viewers to the dangerous journeys millions of animals.
The goal : the survival of their species .
With the latest scientific insights and spectacular images from land ,
aerial and underwater Great Migrations tells the story of species and their survival journey .
Trips that are motivated by the most basic instinct of survival !

The National Geographic team worked no less than two and a half years to the recordings .
And traveled more than 650,000 kilometers on all seven continents .
The result is an equally ambitious and impressive production.
Six hours of stunning images and facts about the migratory behavior of large animals such as :
The Zebras of Botswana elephants in Mali and the great white shark in the Pacific Ocean , to smaller creatures like red crabs on Christmas Island ,
flying foxes in Australia , monarch butterflies , ants pull , plankton , and lots more !
